Based on the skills, expertise, and availability of the team members, the roles and responsibilities within the team could be defined as follows:


1. Chakalov Oleksandr - Project Manager, responsible for overall project planning, progress tracking, and timely delivery.
2. Shevyak Ivan - Backend Developer, responsible for designing and implementing the backend of the trip planner application.
3. Dmytro Hnatyshyn - Frontend Developer, responsible for designing and implementing the user interface of the trip planner application.
4. Anton Vyhovanets - Quality Assurance (QA) Engineer, responsible for ensuring the quality of the application by conducting various tests and identifying bugs.


Roles and responsibilities can be further elaborated in a document, which presents our team with the following details:


•Project Manager (Chakalov Oleksandr):
a.Create and manage the project schedule, including milestones and deadlines.
b.Define project scope and objectives, and ensure that they are met.
c.Identify and manage project risks and issues.
d.Monitor project progress and provide regular status updates to stakeholders.
e.Coordinate and communicate with team members, stakeholders, and third-party vendors.
f.Ensure that the project is delivered on time, within budget, and meets quality standards.
g.Ensure that all project documentation is up-to-date and accurate.

•Backend Developer (Shevyak Ivan):
a.Design, develop, and maintain the backend architecture of the trip planner application.
b.Ensure that the backend components are reliable, scalable, and secure.
c.Collaborate with the front-end developer to integrate the backend components with the user interface.
d.Write and maintain code documentation to ensure that other team members can understand the backend components.
e.Participate in code reviews and other quality assurance activities.
f.Troubleshoot and resolve backend-related issues.

•Frontend Developer (Dmytro Hnatyshyn):
a.Design and implement the user interface of the trip planner application.
b.Ensure that the user interface is user-friendly, accessible, and responsive.
c.Collaborate with the backend developer to integrate the user interface with the backend components.
d.Write and maintain code documentation to ensure that other team members can understand the user interface.
e.Participate in code reviews and other quality assurance activities.
f.Troubleshoot and resolve frontend-related issues.

•Quality Assurance (QA) Engineer (Anton Vyhovanets):
a.Create test plans and test cases to ensure that the trip planner application meets quality standards.
b.Conduct various types of tests to identify bugs and performance issues.
c.Collaborate with the development team to ensure timely resolution of bugs and issues.
d.Ensure that all features of the trip planner application are thoroughly tested before release.
e.Continuously monitor the quality of the application during the development process.
f.Write and maintain documentation related to testing and quality assurance.
g.Participate in code reviews and other quality assurance activities.



By defining and outlining these detailed roles and responsibilities in a document, the team members will have a clear understanding of their tasks and what is expected of them, which will help to ensure that the project is completed successfully and within the specified timeline.
